      },
      "preBlockScreens": [
         "First, we will practice estimating the time you need to click-and-hold. On the following screen, try to click-and-hold on the box for exactly {bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms} ms ({bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms / 1000} second), and then release it.\n\nAs you hold the button, a circle will fill. It will be completely full at exactly {bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms} ms ({bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms / 1000} second). \n\nAfter you release the mouse button you will see the actual time, in miliseconds, that you held for.\n\nThe feedback will be green if you were close to the target time of {bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms} ms ({bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms / 1000} second).\n\nIf the feedback is red, you were too fast.\nIf the feedback is blue, you were too slow.\n\nThe block will end after you make 20 clicks."
      ],
      "repeatAfterBlockScreens": [
        "Remember:\nIf the feedback is red, you were too fast.\nIf the feedback is blue, you were too slow.\n\nPress continue when you are ready for the next set of trials."
      ],
      "repeatUntil": {
        "enabled": true,
        "maxAttempts": 3,
        "minTotal": 20,
        "maxMeanMetric": 0.25,
        "metrics": {
          "correctField": "practice_press_results",
          "metricField": "performance_deltas"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "label": "Practice1",
      "phase": "practice",
      "trials": 4,
      "overrides": {
        "task": {
          "modules": {
            "drt": {
              "enabled": false
            }
          }
        },
        "display": {
          "practiceFeedback": {
            "showHoldProgressCircle": true,
            "holdProgressCircleRadius": 40,
            "holdProgressCircleThickness": 6,
            "holdProgressCircleColor": "#FAFAD2",
            "holdProgressCircleColorOvertime": "#0072B2",
            "holdProgressCircleBgAlpha": 0.05
          }
        }
      },
      "repeatUntil": {
          "enabled": true,
          "maxAttempts": 3,
          "minMeanMetric": 3,
          "metrics": {
            "correctField": "game.stats.cleared",
            "metricField": "game.stats.cleared"
          }
      },
      "repeatAfterBlockScreens": [
        "Let's have another try.\nRemember: you must click and hold inside the highlighted area as many times as required until the box opens. Do this for each box in turn until all boxes have been opened.\n\nHolding for closer to {bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms} ms ({bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms / 1000} second) will clear more of the box.\n"
      ],
      "manipulations": [
        "difficulty_practice",
        "condition_plan"
      ],
      "preBlockScreens": [
        {"html": "<div style='font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif; font-size: 1.2rem; line-height: 1.45;'>Great work!<p><img src='assets/evander-bricks/sprite/boxy_cheer.png' alt='Boxy Cheering' style='max-height: 120px; height: 100%; width: auto;'/></p><p>Now, we will use this same click-and-hold strategy to open some boxes! In the following trials, boxes will move slowly along the conveyor belts. You must click-and-hold for {bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms} ms ({bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms / 1000} second) several times on each box, until it opens. The wider the box, the more work it takes to open. You will still receive feedback on your clicks, but we will no longer show the exact durations.</p>You can only open the box that Boxy has currently highlighted. Once you clear a box, Boxy will highlight another random box for you to work on. Open as many boxes as possible before they are destroyed to maximise your coins!</p><p>After each round, you will be asked to rate your some aspects of your workload and performance on the task. Please carefully read each question, as they ask different things. We encourage you to use the full scale range as the experiment progresses.</p>"},"In the following block there will be four rounds.\nOne round is a full conveyor trial with multiple boxes, followed by a workload questionnaire."
      ],
      "afterBlockScreens": [
        {
          "html": "<div style='font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif; font-size: 1.2rem; line-height: 1.45;'>Well done!<p>As part of this experiment, you will also be asked to respond to a flashing stimulus called the \"DRT\".<p>Whenever you see the border of the experiment window flash red, like this:<p><img src='assets/evander-bricks/drt_border.png' alt='DRT example' style='max-width: 480px; width: 100%; height: auto;'/><p>You should press the SPACEBAR as quickly as possible. This will happen repeatedly throughout the conveyor task.<p></div>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "label": "DRTPractice",
      "phase": "practice",
      "trials": 1,
      "overrides": {
        "display": {
          "practiceFeedback": {
            "showHoldProgressCircle": true,
            "holdProgressCircleRadius": 40,
            "holdProgressCircleThickness": 6,
            "holdProgressCircleColor": "#FAFAD2",
